more about rdl-
- it’s a pure hip hinge movement.

- rather than just thinking about hips back, think about hips and knees back. 

-do not increase the bend in your knees the lower you go. don’t make it a squat.

- don’t reset. 

- stop going down once your hips stop moving backwards.

- always pick the weight from a higher platform rather than ground to save energy.
